Catalysing a Sustainable Shift towards E-Mobility forms part of UNDP’s Climate Promise. The project supports Viet Nam’s targets in its Nationally Determined Contribution (NDC) for the transport sector as well as is aligned with the Ministry of Transport (MOT) Action Programme on Green Transformation and Carbon and Methane Reduction, includes mitigation measures for the transport sector with a focus on modal shift and fuel switch to achieve net zero emission by 2025. The theory of change behind the project is that by promoting and accelerating the shift towards the adoption of EV and clean energy in transport sector will contribute to the achivement of Viet Nam’s targets set in updated NDC. This is done by supporting an enabling environment at both national and city level, delivering capacity building and pilot innovation measures for evidence-based policy formulation, meanwhile raising general public awareness for wider social acceptance.

